      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage advances the travel plot: Kira completes and files the formal inter‑territorial travel request (three hours), receives expedited approval in 18 hours, and is assigned guides who arrive the same day; final medical check and farewells occur and the party departs at dawn into Territory One. I consolidated earlier procedural-detail bullets into a single item about the required documentation and route/protocol structure, updated the timeline to note the unexpected expedition of guide/permission processing, and added a short unresolved-items bullet (Biological Samples, SAM, external comms) to keep outstanding stakes visible. I removed minor atmospheric details and repetitive mentions of form subsections to keep the summary concise and plot‑focused.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle carrying mining/terraforming supplies and a container labeled “Biological Samples” failed during approach; cargo struck the hull and the shuttle crashed; Kira Voss survived while several crew were killed.
          - Shipboard AI SAM is offline; emergency protocols brought Kira’s neural link online and instantiated assistant AI Buddy; external communications and the ship’s distress beacon remain broken.
          - Hull breach exposed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; a plant collective (Scout, Holloway, cooperative spheres, Central Coordination) found Kira, sheltered her, and the shuttle is serving as temporary shelter.
          - The Biological Samples container remains active, glowing, drawing power, and cannot be shut down.
          - Buddy located freshwater; Remedy (salvage-built humanoid doctor) treated Kira’s injured leg; Kira recovered and was medically cleared within a week.
          - Kira integrated with Scout, Holloway, Remedy, Buddy and the collective; the group ran medical/allergy tests and discussed biological protocols and communications.
          - Kira filed a formal petition to Elder Heartwood; Elder Heartwood exists in slow time (responses via relay can take ~8–12 weeks) and is located in the Ancient Grove several territories away.
          - Holloway explained that reaching Elder Heartwood requires filing a formal travel request, securing permissions from each jurisdiction en route, and being assigned experienced guides; the route passes through seven territories with differing administrative protocols and logistics.
          - Earlier travel estimate for the seven‑territory route remains ~21 days of travel (~25 days total with preparations), but initial guide/permission arrangements—originally estimated at 3–4 days—were unexpectedly expedited.
          - Kira spent three hours completing the inter‑territorial travel request (traveler info, route selection, guide specs, inter‑territorial protocols) and submitted it.
          - The request was approved 18 hours later (expedited processing); territorial permissions and guide assignments were confirmed and departure was set for dawn the next day.
          - Two guides were assigned for Territory One: Leafwhisper (mobile, highly communicative, soil/coordination specialist) and Rootwalker (quiet, terrain specialist); they arrived mid‑afternoon.
          - Final preparations and farewells: Remedy performed a final medical check confirming full healing; Florence and the collective offered goodbye/encouragement; Buddy recorded protocols and will accompany; Scout remains a committed companion.
          - At dawn Kira, Scout, Buddy, Leafwhisper, and Rootwalker departed the facility and entered Territory One to begin the inter‑territorial journey; the first day includes significant terrain variation.
          - Outstanding unresolved issues that continue to matter: the active Biological Samples container, SAM remaining offline, and broken external communications/distress beacon; Elder Heartwood’s response/processing timeline remains uncertain.
        </summary>
