          <beat tags="joy, wonder">Kira experiences bright, almost childlike delight while filling out the travel forms and reveling in the micro-bureaucracy. The tactile act of organizing her journey (and Holloway's visible pleasure) converts anxiety into playful competence; the reader shares her amusement and relief at a concrete, controllable step toward agency.</beat>
          <beat tags="hope, relief">An eighteen-hour approval (and guides arriving the same day) produces shocked relief and mounting excitement. This reverses the slow-time expectation and propels immediate anticipation — the POV shifts from planning to imminent departure; the reader feels uplift and quickened tempo.</beat>
          <beat tags="intimacy, vulnerability">Farewells with Florence, Holloway, Remedy and Scout create a tender, slightly bittersweet beat. Kira's throat-tightening at Florence's bloom-language and her last look back before leaving reveal attachment and belonging. The reader experiences warm poignancy — joy tempered by the emotional cost of leaving a found family.</beat>
        </beats>
